More formally, for any given compartment, there cannot be more than one <species> definition in which both of the following hold simultaneously: (i) the <species>' 'compartment' value is set to that compartment's identifier and (ii) the <species>' 'speciesType' is set the same value as the 'speciesType' of another <species> that also sets its 'compartment' to that compartment identifier.
20613.ShortMessage: Cannot have multiple species of the same species type in the same compartment

20614.Message:
The 'compartment' attribute in a <species> is mandatory. A <species> definition in a model must include a value for this attribute. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.3

20615.Message: The 'spatialSizeUnits' attribute on <species>, previously available in SBML Level 2 versions prior to Version 3, has been removed as of SBML Level 2 Version 3.
20615.ShortMessage: Attribute 'spatialSizeUnits' is not supported in this Level+Version of SBML

20616.Message:
If the attribute 'substanceUnits' in a Species object has not been set, then the unit of measurement associated with the species' quantity is determined by the value of the enclosing Model object's 'substanceUnits' attribute. If neither the Species object's 'substanceUnits' attribute nor the enclosing Model object's 'substanceUnits' attribute are set, then the unit of that species' quantity is undefined.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.5
20616.ShortMessage: No substance units defined for the species

20617.Message:
The value of the attribute 'conversionFactor' on a Species object must be the identifier of an existing Parameter object defined in the enclosing Model object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.7

20623.Message:
A Species object must have the required attributes 'id', 'compartment', 'hasOnlySubstanceUnits', 'boundaryCondition' and 'constant', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name', 'initialAmount', 'initialConcentration', 'substanceUnits' and 'conversionFactor'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Species object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6
20623.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on Species object

20701.Message:
The 'units' in a <Parameter> definition must be a value chosen from among the following: a predefined unit (e.g., 'substance', 'time', etc.), the identifier of a <UnitDefinition> in the model, or one of the base units in SBML (e.g., 'litre', 'mole', 'metre', etc.)
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.7.3
20701.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'units' attribute of a Parameter object

20702.Message:
If the attribute 'units' on a given Parameter object has not been set, then the unit of measurement associated with that parameter's value is undefined.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.7.3
20702.ShortMessage: No units defined for the parameter

20705.Message:
A Parameter object referenced by the attribute 'conversionFactor' on a Species or Model object must have a value of 'true' for its attribute 'constant'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.7
20705.ShortMessage: A conversion factor must reference a Parameter object declared to be a constant

20706.Message:
A Parameter object must have the required attributes 'id' and 'constant', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name', 'value' and 'units'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Parameter object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.7
20706.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on Parameter object

20801.Message:
The value of 'symbol' in an <initialAssignment> definition must be the identifier of an existing <compartment>, <species>, or <parameter> defined in the model or <speciesReference> in Level 3.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20801.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'symbol' attribute of an InitialAssignment object

20802.Message:
A given identifier cannot appear as the value of more than one 'symbol' field across the set of <initialAssignment>s in a model.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20802.ShortMessage: Multiple initial assignments for the same 'symbol' value are not allowed

20803.Message:
The value of a 'symbol' field in any <initialAssignment> definition cannot also appear as the value of a 'variable' field in an <assignmentRule>. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20803.ShortMessage: Cannot set a value using both an initial assignment and an assignment rule simultaneously

20804.Message:
An InitialAssignment object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20804.ShortMessage: An InitialAssignment object may contain one <math> element

20805.Message:
An InitialAssignment object must have the required attribute 'symbol' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an InitialAssignment object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20805.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on an InitialAssignment object

20806.Message: The identifier given as the value of a 'symbol' attribute in any <initialAssignment> definition cannot be the identifier of a <compartment> with a 'spatialDimensions' value of 0.

20901.Message:
The value of an <assignmentRule>'s 'variable' must be the identifier of an existing <compartment>, <species>, globally-defined <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference>. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.3
20901.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'variable' attribute of an AssignmentRule object

20902.Message:
The value of a <rateRule>'s 'variable' must be the identifier of an existing <compartment>, <species>, globally-defined <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference>. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.4
20902.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'variable' attribute of a RateRule object

20903.Message:
Any <compartment>, <species>, <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference> whose identifier is the value of a 'variable' attribute in an <assignmentRule>, must have a value of 'false' for 'constant'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.3
20903.ShortMessage: An assignment rule cannot assign an entity declared to be constant

20904.Message:
Any <compartment>, <species>, <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference> whose identifier is the value of a 'variable' attribute in an <rateRule>, must have a value of 'false' for 'constant'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.4
20904.ShortMessage: A rate rule cannot assign an entity declared to be constant

20906.Message:
There must not be circular dependencies in the combined set of <initialAssignment>, <assignmentRule> and <kineticLaw> definitions in a model. Each of these constructs has the effect of assigning a value to an identifier (i.e. the identifier given in the field 'symbol' in <initialAssignment>, the field 'variable' in <assignmentRule>, and the field 'id' on the <kineticLaw>'s enclosing <reaction>). Each of these constructs computes the value using a mathematical formula. The formula for a given identifier cannot make reference to a second identifier whose own definition depends directly or indirectly on the first identifier.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.5
20906.ShortMessage: Circular dependencies involving rules and reactions are not permitted

20907.Message:
Every AssignmentRule, RateRule and AlgebraicRule object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20907.ShortMessage: A rule object may contain one <math> element

20908.Message:
An AssignmentRule object must have the required attribute 'variable' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an AssignmentRule object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20908.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on an AssignmentRule object

20909.Message:
A RateRule object must have the required attribute 'variable' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a RateRule object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20909.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on a RateRule object

20910.Message:
An AlgebraicRule object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an AlgebraicRule object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20910.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on an AlgebraicRule object

20911.Message: The value of a <rateRule> or <assignmentRule>'s 'variable' attribute must not be the identifier of a <compartment> with a 'spatialDimensions' value of 0.

21001.Message:
A <constraint>'s <math> expression must evaluate to a value of type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21001.ShortMessage: A Constraint object's <math> must evaluate to a Boolean value

21002.Message: The order of subelements within <constraint> must be the following: <math>, <message>. The <message> element is optional, but if present, must follow the <math> element.
21002.ShortMessage: Subobjects inside the Constraint object are not in the prescribed order

21003.Message: The contents of the <message> element in a <constraint> must be explicitly placed in the XHTML XML namespace.

21004.Message:
The contents of the <message> element must not contain an XML declaration (i.e., a string of the form "<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>" or similar).
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10.2
21004.ShortMessage: XML declarations are not permitted within Constraint's Message objects

21005.Message:
The contents of the <message> element must not contain an XML DOCTYPE declaration (i.e., a string beginning with the characters "<!DOCTYPE". 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10.2
21005.ShortMessage: XML DOCTYPE elements are not permitted within Constraint's Message objects

21006.Message: The XHTML content inside a <constraint>'s <message> element can only take one of the following general forms: (1) a complete XHTML document beginning with the element <html> and ending with </html>; (2) the "body" portion of a document beginning with the element <body> and ending with </body>; or (3) XHTML content that is permitted within a <body> ... </body> elements.
21006.ShortMessage: Invalid content for a Constraint object's Message object

21007.Message:
A <constraint> object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21007.ShortMessage: A Constraint object may contain one <math> element

21008.Message:
A <constraint> object may contain at most one <message> subobject.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21008.ShortMessage: A Constraint object can only have one Message subobject

21009.Message:
A <constraint> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Constraint object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21009.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on Constraint object

21101.Message:
A <reaction> definition must contain at least one <speciesReference>, either in its <listOfReactants> or its <listOfProducts>. A reaction without any reactant or product species is not permitted, regardless of whether the reaction has any modifier species.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.3
21101.ShortMessage: Cannot have a reaction with neither reactants nor products

21102.Message: The order of subelements within <reaction> must be the following: <listOfReactants> (optional), <listOfProducts> (optional), <listOfModifiers> (optional), <kineticLaw>.
21102.ShortMessage: Subobjects inside the Reaction object are not in the prescribed order

21103.Message:
The following containers are all optional in a <reaction>, but if any is present, it must not be empty: <listOfReactants>, <listOfProducts>, <listOfModifiers>, <kineticLaw>.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21103.ShortMessage: Reaction components, if present, cannot be empty

21104.Message:
The list of reactants (<listOfReactants>) and list of products (<listOfProducts>) in a <reaction> can only contain <speciesReference> elements.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21104.ShortMessage: Invalid object found in the list of reactants or products

21105.Message:
The list of modifiers (<listOfModifiers>) in a <reaction> can only contain <modifierSpeciesReference> elements.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21105.ShortMessage: Invalid object found in the list of modifiers

21106.Message:
A <reaction> object may contain at most one of each of the following elements: <listOfReactants>, <listOfProducts>, <listOfModifiers>, and <kineticLaw>.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21106.ShortMessage: A Reaction object can only contain one of each allowed type of object

21107.Message:
The value of the attribute 'compartment' in a <reaction> object is optional, but if present, must be the identifier of an existing Compartment object defined in the model.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.1
21107.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the Reaction 'compartment' attribute

21110.Message:
A <reaction> object must have the required attributes 'id', 'reversible' and 'fast', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name' and 'compartment'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Reaction object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21110.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute for a Reaction object

21111.Message:
The value of a <speciesReference> 'species' attribute must be the identifier of an existing <species> in the model. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.3
21111.ShortMessage: Invalid 'species' attribute value in SpeciesReference object

21113.Message: A <speciesReference> must not have a value for both 'stoichiometry' and 'stoichiometryMath'; they are mutually exclusive.
21113.ShortMessage: The 'stoichiometry' attribute and StoichiometryMath subobject are mutually exclusive

21116.Message:
A <speciesReference> object must have the required attributes 'species' and 'constant', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name' 'id' and 'stoichiometry'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <speciesReference> object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21116.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the SpeciesReference object

21117.Message:
A <modifierSpeciesReference> object must have the required attribute 'species' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'id' and 'name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <modifierSpeciesReference> object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21117.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ModifierSpeciesReference object

21121.Message:
All species referenced in the <kineticLaw> formula of a given reaction must first be declared using <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference>. More formally, if a <species> identifier appears in a <ci> element of a <reaction>'s <kineticLaw> formula, that same identifier must also appear in at least one <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference> in the <reaction> definition.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.5
21121.ShortMessage: Unknown species referenced in the kinetic law <math> formula

21122.Message: The order of subelements within <kineticLaw> must be the following: <math>, <listOfParameters>. The <listOfParameters> is optional, but if present, must follow <math>.
21122.ShortMessage: Incorrect ordering of components in the KineticLaw object

21123.Message:
If present, the <listOfParameters> in a <kineticLaw> must not be an empty list.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21123.ShortMessage: The list of parameters, if present, cannot be empty

21124.Message: The 'constant' attribute on a <parameter> local to a <kineticLaw> cannot have a value other than 'true'. The values of parameters local to <kineticLaw> definitions cannot be changed, and therefore they are always constant.
21124.ShortMessage: Parameters local to a KineticLaw object must have a 'constant' attribute value of 'true'

21125.Message: The 'substanceUnits' attribute on <kineticLaw>, previously available in SBML Level 1 and Level 2 Version 1, has been removed as of SBML Level 2 Version 2. In SBML Level 2 Version 2, the substance units of a reaction rate expression are those of the global 'substance' units of the model.
21125.ShortMessage: Attribute 'substanceUnits' is not supported in this Level+Version of SBML

21126.Message: The 'timeUnits' attribute on <kineticLaw>, previously available in SBML Level 1 and Level 2 Version 1, has been removed as of SBML Level 2 Version 2. In SBML Level 2 Version 2, the time units of a reaction rate expression are those of the global 'time' units of the model.
21126.ShortMessage: Attribute 'timeUnits' is not supported in this Level+Version of SBML

21127.Message:
A KineticLaw object may contain at most one ListOfLocalParameters container object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21127.ShortMessage: Only one ListOfLocalParameters object is permitted within a KineticLaw object

21128.Message:
Apart from the general Notes and Annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML components, a ListOfLocalParameters container object may only contain LocalParameter objects.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.2.8
21128.ShortMessage: Only LocalParameter, Notes and Annotation objects are allowed in ListOfLocalParameter objects

21129.Message:
A ListOfLocalParameters object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a ListOfLocalParameters object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21129.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ListOfLocalParameters object

21130.Message:
A KineticLaw object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21130.ShortMessage: Only one <math> element is allowed in a KineticLaw object

21131.Message: All species referenced in the <stoichiometryMath> formula of a given reaction must first be declared using <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference>. More formally, if a <species> identifier appears in a <ci> element of a <reaction>'s <stoichiometryMath> formula, that same identifier must also appear in at least one <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference> in the <reaction> definition.
21131.ShortMessage: Unknown species referenced in the StoichiometryMath object's <math> formula

21132.Message:
A KineticLaw object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a KineticLaw object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21132.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the KineticLaw object

21150.Message:
A ListOfSpeciesReferences object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a ListOfSpeciesReferences object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21150.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ListOfSpeciesReferences object

A ListOfModifierSpeciesReferences object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a ListOfModifierSpeciesReferences object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21151.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ListOfModifiers object

21172.Message:
A LocalParameter object must have the required attribute 'id' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name', 'value' and 'units'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a LocalParameter object.

21201.Message:
An <event> object must have a 'trigger'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12.2

21202.Message:
An <event>'s <trigger> expression must evaluate to a value of type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12.2
21202.ShortMessage: A Trigger object's <math> expression must evaluate to a Boolean value

21203.Message:
An <event> object must have at least one <eventAssignment> object in its <listOfEventAssignments>.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21203.ShortMessage: The Event object is missing an EventAssignment subobject

21204.Message: The value of an <event>'s 'timeUnits' attribute must be 'time', 'second', 'dimensionless', or the identifier of a <unitDefinition> derived from either 'second' (with an 'exponent' value of '1') or 'dimensionless'.
21204.ShortMessage: Units referenced by 'timeUnits' attribute are not compatible with units of time

21205.Message: The order of subelements within <event> must be the following: <trigger>, <delay>, <listOfEventAssignments>. The <delay> element is optional, but if present, must follow <trigger>.
21205.ShortMessage: Incorrect ordering of components in Event object

21209.Message:

Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21209.ShortMessage: A Trigger object may have one <math> element

21210.Message:
A Delay object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21210.ShortMessage: A Delay object may have one <math> element

21211.Message:
The value of the attribute 'variable' in an <eventAssignment> can only be the identifier of a <compartment>, <species>, model-wide <parameter> definition, or <speciesReference> in Level 3.

Any <compartment>, <species>, <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference> definition whose identifier is used as the value of 'variable' in an <eventAssignment> must have a value of 'false' for its 'constant' attribute.

21212.ShortMessage: An EventAssignment object cannot assign to a component having attribute 'constant'='true'

21213.Message:
An EventAssignment object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21213.ShortMessage: An EventAssignment object may have one <math> element

21214.Message:
An EventAssignment object must have the required attribute 'variable' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an EventAssignment object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12

80501.Message: As a principle of best modeling practice, the size of a <compartment> should be set to a value rather than be left undefined. Doing so improves the portability of models between different simulation and analysis systems, and helps make it easier to detect potential errors in models.
80501.ShortMessage: It's best to define a size for every compartment in a model

80601.Message: As a principle of best modeling practice, the <species> should set an initial value (amount or concentration) rather than be left undefined. Doing so improves the portability of models between different simulation and analysis systems, and helps make it easier to detect potential errors in models.
80601.ShortMessage: It's best to define an initial amount or initial concentration for every species in a model

80701.Message: As a principle of best modeling practice, the units of a <parameter> should be declared rather than be left undefined. Doing so improves the ability of software to check the consistency of units and helps make it easier to detect potential errors in models.
80701.ShortMessage: It's best to declare units for every parameter in a model

80702.Message: As a principle of best modeling practice, the <parameter> should set an initial value rather than be left undefined. Doing so improves the portability of models between different simulation and analysis systems, and helps make it easier to detect potential errors in models.
80702.ShortMessage: It's best to declare values for every parameter in a model

Modelers may wish to take precautions to avoid this happening accidentally.
81121.ShortMessage: Local parameters defined within a kinetic law shadow global object symbols
